                <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #8B5CF6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <strong>📋 What to Bring:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 10px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li><strong>Swimming essentials:</strong> Swimsuit, towel, change of clothes</li>
                        <li><strong>Footwear:</strong> Comfortable walking shoes (water shoes recommended for pools)</li>
                        <li><strong>Sun protection:</strong> Sunscreen (SPF 50+), sunglasses, hat</li>
                        <li><strong>Camera:</strong> Waterproof camera or phone case for pool photos</li>
                        <li><strong>Snacks:</strong> Light refreshments and water (also available for purchase)</li>
                        <li><strong>Cash:</strong> Small amount for optional purchases or tips</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #d1ecf1; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #8B5CF6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <strong>ℹ️ Good to Know:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 10px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li><strong>Best time to visit:</strong> Year-round destination; mornings less crowded (spring & fall ideal for temperature)</li>
                        <li><strong>Difficulty level:</strong> Easy to moderate; suitable for families with children 6+</li>
                        <li><strong>Swimming ability:</strong> Not required but swimming enhances the experience</li>
                        <li><strong>Water temperature:</strong> Cool and refreshing (18-22°C / 64-72°F)</li>
                        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Requires moderate walking on uneven terrain; not wheelchair accessible</li>
                        <li><strong>Group size:</strong> Small groups (max 15 people) for personalized experience</li>
                        <li><strong>Free cancellation:</strong> Cancel up to 24 hours before departure for full refund</li>
                        <li><strong>Languages:</strong> Tours conducted in English and French</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div style="background: #e8f5e9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #8B5CF6;">
                    <strong>💡 Local Insider Tips:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 10px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>Arrive early (9 AM departure) for the best experience and fewer crowds</li>
                        <li>The water is coolest in the morning – perfect for hot days!</li>
                        <li>Bring a waterproof bag to keep your valuables dry</li>
                        <li>Local vendors sell fresh fruit and drinks – support the community</li>
                        <li>Some pools have natural "slides" – your guide will show you the safe ones</li>
                        <li>Don't rush – take time to enjoy the peaceful atmosphere</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Things to Do in Jet Ski Section -->
            <div class="tour-description">
                <h2>Things to Do in Jet Ski Agadir</h2>
                <p>Jet Ski offers numerous activities for visitors of all ages and interests:</p>
                
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">🏊 Swimming & Water Activities</h3>
                <p>The valley features multiple natural pools carved by centuries of water flow. Some pools are shallow and perfect for relaxing, while others are deep enough for swimming and diving. The water is crystal clear, allowing you to see the rocky bottom, and remains cool even in summer months – a refreshing escape from Agadir's heat.</p>

                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">🥾 Hiking & Nature Walks</h3>
                <p>Explore the valley on foot along scenic trails that wind through palm groves and along the riverbed. The hiking is generally easy, with some sections requiring scrambling over rocks. Your guide will lead you to the best viewpoints and hidden spots that most tourists miss.</p>

                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">📸 Photography & Sightseeing</h3>
                <p>Jet Ski is a photographer's dream. Capture stunning images of turquoise pools, dramatic rock formations, lush greenery, and local wildlife. The play of light through the palm leaves creates magical photo opportunities, especially in the morning.</p>

                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">🧗 Cliff Jumping (Optional)</h3>
                <p>For adventure seekers, several pools offer safe cliff-jumping spots ranging from 1 to 8 meters. Your guide will point out the safe areas and depth requirements. This is entirely optional and only recommended for confident swimmers.</p>

                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">🌴 Berber Culture Experience</h3>
                <p>Visit a traditional Berber village along the route, meet local families, and learn about their lifestyle. Enjoy authentic Moroccan hospitality with mint tea and see how argan oil is traditionally produced.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Visit Jet Ski Section -->
            <div class="tour-description">
                <h2>Planning Your Visit to Jet Ski Morocco</h2>
                
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">Best Time to Visit Jet Ski</h3>
                <p>Jet Ski can be visited year-round, but each season offers a unique experience:</p>
                <ul style="margin-left: 25px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <li><strong>Spring (March-May):</strong> Perfect weather, blooming flowers, moderate water levels – ideal for swimming and hiking</li>
                    <li><strong>Summer (June-August):</strong> Hot days make the cool water especially refreshing; can be busier but still enjoyable</li>
                    <li><strong>Fall (September-November):</strong> Pleasant temperatures, fewer tourists, golden light for photography</li>
                    <li><strong>Winter (December-February):</strong> Mild weather, very few tourists, water is cold but scenery is spectacular</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">How Far is Jet Ski from Agadir?</h3>
                <p>Jet Ski is located approximately 30 kilometers (19 miles) north of Agadir, which translates to about 30-40 minutes by car depending on traffic. The journey itself is scenic, passing through Aourir (Banana Village) and into the Atlas Mountain foothills. The road is paved and well-maintained.</p>

                <h3 style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #1F2937;">Why Book a Guided Tour vs. Independent Visit?</h3>
                <p>While it's possible to reach Jet Ski independently, our guided tour offers significant advantages:</p>
                <ul style="margin-left: 25px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                    <li><strong>No parking hassle:</strong> Limited parking at the valley entrance can be difficult</li>
                    <li><strong>Expert guidance:</strong> Know exactly where to go and discover hidden spots</li>
                    <li><strong>Safety first:</strong> Local guides know which pools are safe for swimming and jumping</li>
                    <li><strong>Cultural context:</strong> Learn about the area's history, geology, and local culture</li>
                    <li><strong>Time optimization:</strong> Make the most of your visit with insider knowledge</li>
                    <li><strong>Stress-free:</strong> Just enjoy – we handle all logistics</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="faq-section">
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Jet Ski Agadir</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        How long does the Jet Ski tour take?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The complete Jet Ski Agadir tour lasts approximately 4-5 hours, including round-trip transportation from Agadir. You'll spend about 2-2.5 hours exploring the valley, swimming, and hiking, with 30-40 minutes travel time each way.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Is Jet Ski suitable for children and families?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! Jet Ski is great for families with children aged 6 and above. The shallow pools are perfect for kids, and the hiking trails are manageable for most children. However, close supervision is required near deeper pools and rocks. Many families enjoy this as one of their favorite things to do in Jet Ski Agadir.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Do I need to know how to swim to enjoy Jet Ski?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>No, swimming is not required! Jet Ski has pools of varying depths. There are shallow pools where you can simply wade and relax, and deeper pools for those who want to swim. You can still enjoy the hiking, scenery, photography, and cultural experience even if you don't swim.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        What should I wear for the Jet Ski day trip from Agadir?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Wear comfortable walking shoes (water shoes are ideal), bring a swimsuit under your clothes, and dress modestly (Morocco is a Muslim country). Bring a hat, sunglasses, and sunscreen. We recommend bringing a small backpack for your towel and change of clothes.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Is the water in Jet Ski clean and safe?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! The water in Jet Ski comes from natural mountain springs and is crystal clear, fresh, and safe for swimming. The pools are naturally filtered by the rocks and constantly refreshed by flowing water. Many visitors describe it as some of the cleanest natural water they've experienced.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Can I visit Jet Ski from Taghazout as well as Agadir?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely! We offer pickup from both Agadir and Taghazout, as well as surrounding areas. Taghazout is actually even closer to Jet Ski (about 20 minutes), making it a convenient half-day excursion for surfers and beach lovers staying in the area.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        How difficult is the hike in Jet Ski?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The hike is rated easy to moderate. The trails are generally well-established, though some sections require walking on rocks and uneven terrain. Most visitors with average fitness can comfortably complete the hike. Take your time, wear appropriate footwear, and let your guide know if you need to rest.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        What time should I book my Jet Ski tour?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We highly recommend the 9:00 AM departure for the best experience. Morning visits offer cooler temperatures, fewer crowds, better light for photography, and you'll have the afternoon free for other activities. We also offer afternoon departures if mornings don't work for you.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Is food available at Jet Ski?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Local vendors at the entrance sell fresh fruit, nuts, drinks, and light snacks at reasonable prices. However, there are no restaurants at the valley itself. We include mint tea and bread at a Berber house, but we recommend bringing additional snacks if you have specific dietary needs or preferences.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Can I combine Jet Ski with other Agadir tours?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes! Since this is a half-day tour ending around 1-2 PM, you can combine it with afternoon activities like a sunset camel ride, quad biking, or visiting Agadir's Souk El Had market. Ask us about combo tour packages to save money and maximize your time!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

